   <note>2 tifs. A color on photograph postcard of the Spofford House, in Pulaski, Tennessee where the Ku Klux Klan was organized. The card is a photograph that is painted in fall hues. The street in front of the house is lined with open-air cars, and the house is a brick structure with ornate stone details around the windows and doors. The verso is blank, but bears a green one cent Benjamin Franklin stamp, and the Copyright by Richardson, Pulaski, Tenn.</note>
